sume that staple-based development comprises only "good" and "bad" staples that inevitably lead to development and underdevelopment respectively. She has instead produced a rich and complex analysis which broadens our understanding of colonial staple development and commodity trade and introduces new insights on regional development.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCod-fisheriesxEconomic aspectszQuébec (Province)zGaspé. 0aFish tradezChannel IslandszJerseyxHistory. 0aFish tradezQuébec (Province)zGaspéxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Canada / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077356227140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773562271423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773562271/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles